ating run of the Olympics, and they miss the world record by just a tenth of a second in 3:15.27.\", \"from\": 2408, \"to\": 2524, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the most dominating run\", \"from\": 2413, \"to\": 2436}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2452}, {\"ngram\": \"the world record\", \"from\": 2468, \"to\": 2484}, {\"ngram\": \"just a tenth\", \"from\": 2488, \"to\": 2500}, {\"ngram\": \"a second\", \"from\": 2504, \"to\": 2512}, {\"ngram\": \"3:15.27\", \"from\": 2516, \"to\": 2523}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They will settle for an American record and gold medal!\", \"from\": 2525, \"to\": 2580, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2549, \"end\": 2557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999991854405059, \"rank\": 8.144562841264987e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bol kicks for the silver as the Netherlands sets a national record, 3:19.50.\", \"from\": 2582, \"to\": 2658, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2614, \"end\": 2625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9928822200160442, \"rank\": 0.007168802568027728, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Bol kicks\", \"from\": 2582, \"to\": 2591}, {\"ngram\": \"the silver\", \"from\": 2596, \"to\": 2606}, {\"ngram\": \"a national record\", \"from\": 2631, \"to\": 2648}, {\"ngram\": \"3:19.50\", \"from\": 2650, \"to\": 2657}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And for bronze it's another national record for the British team and Amber Anning, 3:19.72.\", \"from\": 2659, \"to\": 2750, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 271